**Problem**: In content.js, if any fill operation throws an error, setFilling(false) never runs, leaving the extension permanently stuck in "filling" state. The SPA observer skips fills while __jcFilling is true.

**Files to modify**: 
- /Users/shivam94/job-copilot/extension/content/content.js

**Fix required**:
1. Find the Fill All execution chain (likely in panel UI click handler and message handler)
2. Wrap the async fill chain in try/finally blocks
3. Ensure setFilling(false) always runs even if individual fills throw
4. Add error logging so we can see what failed

**Example pattern**:
```javascript
// Before (broken):
setFilling(true);
await fillPersonal();
await fillExperience();
// ... more fills
setFilling(false); // Never runs if above throws

// After (fixed):
setFilling(true);
try {
  await fillPersonal();
  await fillExperience();
  // ... more fills
} catch (err) {
  console.error('[JC] Fill chain error:', err);
} finally {
  setFilling(false); // Always runs
}
```

Apply this pattern to ALL fill chains in content.js. Check both:
1. Panel UI Fill All button handler
2. Message handler for Fill All requests

Also check if there are individual section fill functions that could throw and need try/catch.

